OL,3,CDoctors divided in Jersey's assisted
OL,4,Cdying debate
OL,6,F"An example I would give is motor
OL,7,Fneurone disease. I don't know how I
OL,8,Fmight act should I develop it but I
OL,9,Fhave two daughters and I know that I
OL,10,Fwould not want them, out of love, to
OL,11,Fwatch me diminish in front of them to
OL,12,Fthe point that I drowned in my own
OL,13,Fspit.
OL,15,F"However well those symptoms are
OL,16,Fcontrolled, that would be the lasting
OL,17,Fimpression they had of their father so
OL,18,FI'm pretty sure if that choice was
OL,19,Foffered and I had that awful disease,
OL,20,FI would take it."
