OL,3,CDoctors divided in Jersey's assisted
OL,4,Cdying debate
OL,6,FDr Andreas Melchior is an experienced
OL,7,FJersey GP who is against assisted
OL,8,Fdying and believes the focus should be
OL,9,Fon saving lives rather than ending
OL,10,Fthem prematurely.
OL,12,FHe explains: "I understand that people
OL,13,Fwith motor neurone disease or other
OL,14,Fdeteriorating neurological conditions
OL,15,Fwill feel fearful.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G4/6
