OL,3,CDoctors divided in Jersey's assisted
OL,4,Cdying debate
OL,6,F"It's a horrible disease but there are
OL,7,Fphysiotherapists who look after them
OL,8,Fand there are people with those
OL,9,Fdiseases who choose not to terminate
OL,10,Ftheir own life who are actually
OL,11,Ffearful that they would be
OL,12,Fdiscriminated against and suggested to
OL,13,Fchoose an assisted death.
OL,15,F"I think once we cross that line and
OL,16,Fwe become the ones that decide, that's
OL,17,Fa very dangerous move and it erodes
OL,18,Fthe Hippocratic Oath to do no harm."
